utterance:
That's so; it was suthin' like a thousand francs;
but French money, when you pan it out as dollars and
cents, don't make so much, after all.

But that was fighting Nature, not patronising her;
and it's a business that pays. That reminds me that I
must go back to it.

I am afraid we are both old fools, Mr. Sharpe;
but-we will talk this over with Lady Mainwaring.
Come
